00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:04,120
英文：Lesson 143.
中文：课143。

2
00:00:04,219 --> 00:00:06,500
英文：A walk through the woods.
中文：穿过树林散步。

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,960
英文：Listen to the tape, then answer this question.
中文：听录音，然后回答问题。

4
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:16,740
英文：What was so funny about the words on the sign?
中文：招牌上的字有什么好笑的？

5
00:00:19,179 --> 00:00:24,500
英文：I live in a very old town, which is surrounded by beautiful woods.
中文：我住在一个非常古老的小镇，周围环绕着美丽的树林。

6
00:00:24,879 --> 00:00:27,039
英文：It is a famous beauty spot.
中文：这是一个著名的景点。

7
00:00:27,839 --> 00:00:34,399
英文：On Sundays, hundreds of people come from the city to see our town and to walk through the woods.
中文：星期天，数百人从城里来参观我们的小镇，穿过树林。

8
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:39,539
英文：Visitors have been asked to keep the woods clean and tidy.
中文：游客们被要求保持树林干净整洁。

9
00:00:40,539 --> 00:00:46,419
英文：Little baskets have been placed under the trees, but people still throw their rubbish everywhere.
中文：树下已经放了小篮子，但人们仍然到处乱扔垃圾。

10
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:50,419
英文：Last Wednesday, I went for a walk in the woods.
中文：上周三，我去林中散步。

11
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:54,019
英文：What I saw made me very sad.
中文：我所看到的让我非常难过。

12
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:59,439
英文：I counted seven old cars and three old refrigerators.
中文：我数了数七辆旧车和三台旧冰箱。

13
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:11,619
英文：The litter baskets were empty and the ground was covered with pieces of paper, cigarette ends, old tires, empty bottles and rusty tins.
中文：垃圾篮是空的，地上满是纸片、烟头、旧轮胎、空瓶子和生锈的罐头。

14
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:20,719
英文：Among the rubbish, I found a sign which said, anyone who leaves litter in these woods will be prosecuted.
中文：在垃圾中，我发现了一块牌子，上面写着：任何在这些树林里乱扔垃圾的人都会被起诉。

